3 the fund at the end of the fiscal year shall remain in the fund.
4 E. Monies in the fund shall be appropriated to the Coastal Protection
5 and Restoration Authority for use by the board of commissioners for the Amite
6 River Basin Drainage and Water Conservation District for use as provided in
7 Subsection B of this Section.
8 F. An annual report detailing the receipts, expenditures, and funded
9 activities of the Watershed Restoration and Conservation Fund shall be
10 submitted by the board to the House Committee on Natural Resources and
11 Environment and the Senate Committee on Natural Resources by March first
12 of each calendar year.
13 Section 2. This Act shall become effective on July 1, 2026.
